Title: Roofed porches on the 1st floor

Subheading: How to determine if a porch is at least 50% open (using Fig 5 as an example)

Figure label: Fig 5  Roofed 1st floor porch

Step 1 text: Determine the perimeter of the porch and divide it into segments that will allow a comparison of closed and open segments.

Perimeter note: The perimeter of the porch in Fig 5 is shown below. It is the sum of segments A through G. It is 70 linear feet.

Plan diagram segment labels and dimensions shown:
- A: 2'
- B: 8'
- C: 10'
- D: 7'
- E: 14'
- F: 24'
- G: 2'
